	<tr>
		
			<td colspan="2" bgcolor="#DEDACB" background="http://www.everlore.com/gimages/tb_beige.gif">
		
				<font face="verdana" size="2" color="black">
				to answer the post regarding the question of buffs<BR>
versus AC...always go for buffs..period...unless the buff is less than 2 and the AC loss greater than 3...i wouldnt even consider trading buff items for straight AC...<BR>
<BR>
the reasoning is simple...look at the percentages.<BR>
<BR>
the +5 STA , in this case, represents AT LEAST a<BR>
5% increase in that stat.  whereas a 2 pt loss of<BR>
AC becomes trivial at levels 7 and up...if your AC<BR>
is greater than 200, a 2 pt. loss represents a less than 1 percent loss in that stat.  also, AC is buffered every level for us tanks, due to increases in defense scores at 5 per level, which is about 10 or more pts in AC per level...at level<BR>
20...choosing armor items solely for high AC will get you killed, and often.<BR>
<BR>
AC only helps you partially absorb damage from blows recieved...it does little to prevent them in<BR>
the first place.<BR>
<BR>
the +5 STA is especially useful for a high elf paladin, as your base STA is probably pretty low.<BR>
<BR>
STA increases act as a sort of buffer for your agility...keeping you able to withstand long fight<BR>
durations whilst your yellow bar stays yellow...as<BR>
you lose that yellow bar...notice your agility drop SEVERELY.<BR>
<BR>
and don't forget the &quot;freebie&quot; STA buffs give...a<BR>
few extra hitpoints...not many...but havent you ever zoned out with 2 hitpoints?  i have...10 more<BR>
would've been not so bad to have.<BR>
<BR>
this is not a power character's choice belt...but it helps if you are soloing...or if you just dont<BR>
have a better choice...<BR>
<BR>
if you can wear a purity belt(medium only), go for that instead...<BR>
<BR>
but if you cant...a thick leather apron can be had<BR>
for 20pp or less on fennin ro...<BR>
<BR>
the BI girdle sells for 40-50p, and i would wear one over a thick apron...but purity belt is the cheapo choice...2 STA , 2 STR, AC3...and only 3-4pp!!<BR>
<BR>
there you have it...my take on Stamina, buffs vs. AC, and belts for under 100pp<BR>
<BR>
thomaas archonian<BR>
fennin ro<BR>
keishan sect high council officer<BR>
level 30 paladin<BR>
weilder of ghoulbane and many other fine trinkets
				</font>
			</td>

	</tr>
	
